00:30:22.729 --> 00:30:27.559
when we delve into the field of psychology.
And we learn that psychologists have identified

00:30:27.559 --> 00:30:32.320
there's six universal
human needs to thrive.

00:30:32.320 --> 00:30:34.729
The first three are respect, recognition,
and belonging.

00:30:34.729 --> 00:30:39.719
They're relational needs.
And when -- and in our research, what we discovered

00:30:39.719 --> 00:30:43.349
is that when these
needs are being met people inevitably described

00:30:43.349 --> 00:30:47.719
that they clicked or
they connected with the people they worked

00:30:47.719 --> 00:30:52.909
with.
The next two needs are task mastery needs.

00:30:52.909 --> 00:30:57.480
They are autonomy and personal growth.
And when people experience, when these needs

00:30:57.480 --> 00:31:02.159
are being met, people
describe it was feeling connected or immersed

00:31:02.159 --> 00:31:06.200
in their day-to-day work.
