00:46:04.859 --> 00:46:08.460
together like we did today in small groups
and just talk through.

00:46:08.460 --> 00:46:11.069
And that helps us all learn and better understand
connection.

00:46:11.069 --> 00:46:17.269
Who will you choose to become?
That's the question I want to leave you with

00:46:17.269 --> 00:46:20.480
today.
Because becoming an intentional connector

00:46:20.480 --> 00:46:23.770
is a choice.
I think of people as falling into three categories

00:46:23.770 --> 00:46:25.789
what it comes to
connection.

00:46:25.789 --> 00:46:30.519
The first is unintentional -- I'm sorry.
Intentional disconnectors.

00:46:30.519 --> 00:46:34.849
These are the individuals who lie, cheat,
and steal for self benefit.

00:46:34.849 --> 00:46:37.039
And some are psychopaths.
Some are sociopaths.

00:46:37.039 --> 00:46:42.280
Some are close to that.
Some, some are -- the abrasive disconnectors

00:46:42.280 --> 00:46:47.670
you'll be able to spot.
But others are smooth and cunning, and you

00:46:47.670 --> 00:46:51.950
have to watch your back.
With intentional disconnectors, because they

00:46:51.950 --> 00:46:54.099
have learned how to
navigate in organizations, and you're going

00:46:54.099 --> 00:46:57.920
to run into them.
The second group is where most of us fall,

00:46:57.920 --> 00:47:01.200
what we call the
unintentional disconnectors.

00:47:01.200 --> 00:47:04.849
Because we all have blind spots, we don't
see.

00:47:04.849 --> 00:47:10.609
There are things we do that promote disconnection.
It may be that we're overly critical.

00:47:10.609 --> 00:47:15.910
It may be that we are not effective in giving
or receiving honest

00:47:15.910 --> 00:47:21.109
feedback.
Those things create disconnection in relationships.

00:47:21.109 --> 00:47:25.470
And we need people around us who will give
us honest feedback and help

00:47:25.470 --> 00:47:29.380
us improve in those areas.
And when we do, when we're intentional about

00:47:29.380 --> 00:47:32.820
learning about connection,
and surrounding ourselves with individuals

00:47:32.820 --> 00:47:36.109
who will give us honest
feedback, that helps us reach the pentacle

00:47:36.109 --> 00:47:40.990
of connection which is the
intentional connector.

00:47:40.990 --> 00:47:47.539
I wholeheartedly believe with, after doing
all the research, and

00:47:47.539 --> 00:47:52.230
thinking about my own experiences in life
and in work, that if we're

00:47:52.230 --> 00:47:55.500
intentional about focussing on developing
task excellence and

00:47:55.500 --> 00:48:00.779
relationship excellence through connection,
we will perform at the top

00:48:00.779 --> 00:48:04.049
of our game whether we're an organization
or an individual.

00:48:04.049 --> 00:48:09.540
And my hope for you today is that you will
become an intentional

00:48:09.540 --> 00:48:12.529
connector.
That you'll become an intentional connector

00:48:12.529 --> 00:48:16.059
not only here among your
colleagues at Google but also among your family

00:48:16.059 --> 00:48:19.309
members at home.
